28/12/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- A homemade bomb exploded late Sunday (December 27th) in front of the offices of the national bank and insurance agency in Athens' Neos Kosmos district, damaging the building and nearby cars. 
"There was a phone warning received in a local newspaper about 15 minutes before the explosion but nobody has claimed responsibility for the attack," police said. 
Injuries were avoided as the police cordoned off the area after the warning. 
(ANA-MPA - 28/12/09; DPA, Deutsche Welle, Reuters, AFP - 27/12/09)
